02/11/2007
The Greek food and drinks producer Vivartia plans to invest 800m euros in the expansion of its activities in Southeast Europe. The investments will be made between 2008 and 2012, especially in the dairy markets of Bulgaria and Cyprus. 
*** 
The World Bank has approved a new, 50m-euro International Bank for Reconstruction and Development loan and a Global Efficiency Facility grant of 3.8m euros for the Integrated Nutrient Pollution Control project in Romania. Total project costs have been estimated at 56.4m euros. 
*** 
The volume of trade between Romania and Turkey could reach 4.5 billion euros by the end of this year and increase further to 6.9 billion euros in 2010, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said at the Romanian-Turkish Business Forum in Bucharest on Friday (October 26th). Trade volume in the first nine months of 2007 grew 40% year-on-year. 
*** 
Slovenian household appliances producer Gorenje plans to build a washing machine factory in Valjevo, Serbia. Gorenje already has a plant for production of refrigerators and freezers in Valjevo, which produced 500,000 units last year. 
*** 
Serbia might end the year with a budget surplus, instead of a deficit as projected, due to slower execution of the National Investment Plan, Finance Minister Mirko Cvetkovic said on Monday (October 29th). 
*** 
Household savings in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) banks reached 2.4m euros at the end of September, according to BiH Deposit Insurance Agency data. The total savings of the population increased by 350m euros or 17%. According to the agency, the total deposit base at the banks amounted to 6.8 billion euros. 
